div.div: Mushoku Tensei II: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu

The second season of Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu. Rudeus heads north with new friends and powers in search of adventure and those he once knew. (Source: Crunchyroll) Note: Includes episode 0.
Akuyaku Reijou Level 99: Watashi wa Ura Boss desu ga Maou de wa Arimasen

This college kid wants nothing more than a quiet life. So when she’s reborn as Yumiella, the hidden villainess of an Otome RPG, she’s not exactly thrilled. Still yearning for peace, she abandons her evil duties to live a more discreet life. Until her gamer side kicks in and she accidentally reaches level 99! Now, everyone suspects that she’s the infamous Demon Lord. What future awaits her?
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Isekai ni Kyuuseishu to Shite Yobaremashita ga, Arasa ni wa Muri nano de, Hissori Book Cafe Hajimemashita.
Comedy, Drama, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

When a “god” tells Tsukina that she is to be transported to another world to become its savior, Tsukina isn’t interested. As a bookish thirty-something, she has zero desire to go on some big adventure…so when she arrives in the strange new land, she decides to use her magical powers to create a cozy little book café instead. But when a fellow “savior” starts causing trouble, Tsukina might just have to play the hero, after all! (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment) Note: Includes 4 extra chapters.

Shikimori seems like the perfect girlfriend: cute, fun to be around, sweet when she wants to be… but she has a cool dark side that comes out under the right circumstances. And her boyfriend Izumi loves to be around when that happens! (Source: Kodansha USA) Notes: - Chapter count includes 25 extra chapters. - The work was first self-published by the author on their Twitter account. - It began its official publication in Pocket Magazine on February 2, 2019. - Won 5th place in Tsugimanga 2020 Award in the Web Manga Category.
